Package net.marfgamer.raknet.exception.client

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AlreadyConnectedException
    This exception is thrown whenever the client is attempting to connect to a server it is already connected to
    ConnectionBannedException
    This exception is thrown when the client is banned from the server it is attempting to connect to
    EncryptionEnabledException Deprecated
    IncompatibleProtocolException
    This exception is thrown when the client does not share the same protocol as the server it is attempting to connect to
    InvalidProtocolException
    This exception is thrown whenever the client receives a broken login packet from an online server during login, it is important that this is distinguished from IncompatibleProtocolException, as this exception means that the expected packet format/data was invalid while IncompatibleProtocolException means that the server or client is outdated
    NettyHandlerException
    This exception is thrown whenever the RakNetClientHandler catches an exception caused by the server the client is attempting to connect to
    NoFreeIncomingConnectionsException
    This exception is thrown whenever the server the client is attempting to connect to is full
    PacketBufferException
    This exception is thrown whenever a critical packet fails to encode or decode correctly
    ServerOfflineException
    This exception is thrown whenever the server the client is attempting to is offline
    UseSecurityException Deprecated
